Based on my analysis, this bug requires `CONFIG_PREEMPTION=y` to manifest (double scheduling from `spin_unlock()` preemption + explicit `preempt_schedule_common()`), but kSTEP builds with `CONFIG_PREEMPT_NONE=y`. With PREEMPT_NONE, both buggy and fixed code call `preempt_schedule_common()` exactly once, making them behaviorally identical. Even with CONFIG_PREEMPT, the second `__schedule()` call doesn't produce an externally observable context switch.

